entries.title: Brazil Riot Investigators Probe Possible Crimes
entries.description: Prosecutors are attempting to determine whether there was a coordinated plan to take power.

entries.title: China's Economic Reopening Complicates the Global Fight Against Inflation
entries.description: A stronger Chinese economy would boost demand for commodities but could also ease supply-chain bottlenecks—resulting in mixed signals for central bankers

entries.title: Israel's Netanyahu Fires Key Ally in Challenge for New Government
entries.description: The move, prompted by a Supreme Court ruling, threatens the stability of the newly sworn-in conservative coalition.

entries.title: Russia Claims Advances in Ukraine's South
entries.description: Moscow said its forces advanced in Ukraine’s southern Zaporizhzhia region as Kyiv’s Western allies continued pressuring Berlin to allow deliveries of German-made tanks to Ukraine.

entries.title: Europe's Leaders Are in Battle of Wills Over Ukraine War
entries.description: Fear of receding U.S. support for Kyiv is raising pressure in Europe for bolder action.
